    Use experiments/adaptive_policy_search.py to grid-search thresholds/n_high, then feed the chosen parameters via the flags above.

  Notes / future hooks

  - The adaptive override is opt-in; defaults remain the previous heuristic. We can formalize “adaptive_policy_v1” by wiring a policy
    file/ID, but the flags cover immediate testing.
  - Plots use matplotlib only; no pandas introduced. Heatmaps assume regular sigma/R grids; missing cells render as blanks.
  - For the “real weights” story, export W and x_batch from a small trained model to .npz and run the quant lab + plots to get
    loss_delta vs R and robustness curves.
